images.alt:
Claude is not an image model and cannot generate images. It’s a text-based model that can analyse images shared with it, but it only produces text, code, documents, and similar outputs – never images.

ChatGPT has DALL-E integration and Gemini has Imagen, which are image generation capabilities. Claude has no equivalent. So grouping Claude with those two as “image models” to test image generation moderation policies is either a mistake or a misunderstanding of what Claude actually is.​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​
